efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution utilizes a stack to efficiently track previous prices. For each new price, it iterates through the stack, comparing it to the current price. The span is incremented as long as the previous price is less than or equal to the current price. This approach ensures a linear time complexity as it only iterates through a maximum of N previous prices. The space complexity is also linear due to the storage of previous prices in the stack.

